Package de.dedede.model.logic.util

Class TrespassListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.dedede.model.logic.util.TrespassListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    jakarta.faces.event.PhaseListener, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener
    public class TrespassListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements jakarta.faces.event.PhaseListener
    Checks user requests based on loginstatus, UserRole and the requested page of the application. It denies access to pages where the UserDto has no rights for. Uses the session map to check the loginstatus of the user. Checks the user role by checking the actual class of the user (UserDto, NormalUser, Admin, LibraryStaff. The user roles are structured as in the following: NormalUser - LibraryStaff - Admin. The user role can access all pages of them. If a lower role navigates to a page, where he has no rights for a message appears that this page does not exists.
